  <br><br>
  <section id="projectSection" class="py-sm-2 py-md-3 py-lg-4">
    <br>
    <div class="grid-container usa-section">
      <div class="grid-row grid-gap">
	<div class="tablet:grid-col-4">
	  <h1 class="font-heading-xl margin-top-0 tablet:margin-bottom-0">The Project</h1>
	</div>
	<div class="tablet:grid-col-8 usa-prose">
	  <p>This website is a tool created that allows users to sign up to receive notifcations when post cost of living allowance (COLA) rates for change. This app monitors COLA rates found at <a class="usa-link usa-link--alt usa-link--external" href="https://aoprals.state.gov/Web920/cola.asp">aoprals.state.gov</a>. Users can subscribe to one or more posts and will receive email notifications when COLA rates to these posts change. </p>
	  <p>This web app was created as a VSFS project in collaboration with the US Embassy Gaborone in Botswana. For more information on the VSFS program, see <a class="usa-link usa-link--alt usa-link--external" href="https://vsfs.state.gov/">here</a>.</p>
	</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br>
  </section>
  <section id="faqSection" class="mt-4 py-4">
    <div class="container d-flex inlineBlock">
      <h1 class="h2 border-bottom px-2 pt-4 pb-2"> Frequently Asked Questions </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="container mb-4">
      <div class="row mt-4">
	<div class="col">
	  <div class="usa-accordion faq-accordion">
	    <h2 class="usa-accordion__heading">
              <button class="usa-accordion__button faq-accordion-button"
		      aria-expanded="true"
		      aria-controls="a2">
		<span class="font-xl" style="font-weight: lighter">Q.</span>
		What are the templates?
              </button>
	    </h2>
	    <div id="a2" class="usa-accordion__content usa-prose">
              <p>Templates are .doc or .docx files that will be updated with new COLA rates and emailed to subscriber upon COLA rates changing.</p>
	      <p>When creating a new subscription to a post, users are presented with the option of either using a <a class="usa-link previewDefaultTemplate" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#previewTemplateModal">default template</a>, or uploading a customized template. <a class="usa-link" id="jumpToTemplateLooks" href="#templateLooks">What should my customized template look like</a>?</p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	  <div id="templateLooks" class="usa-accordion faq-accordion">
	    <h2 class="usa-accordion__heading">
              <button class="usa-accordion__button faq-accordion-button"
		      aria-expanded="false"
		      aria-controls="a3">
		<span class="font-xl" style="font-weight: lighter">Q.</span>
		What should my template look like?
              </button>
	    </h2>
	    <div id="a3" class="usa-accordion__content usa-prose">
              <p>A sample template can be viewed <a class="usa-link previewDefaultTemplate" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#previewTemplateModal">here</a>.</p>
	      <p>Uploaded templates should be .doc or .docx format. Prior to sending email to subscriber, the app will complete various fields in the user's template. Fields are shown below. Each field must be wrapped in curly braces (eg {field}) in uploaded template file. </p>
	      <p>
		<div class="row ml-4">
		  <table id="syntaxTable" class="usa-table">
		    <thead>
		      <tr>
			<th scope="col">Field</th>
			<th scope="col">File syntax</th>
		      </tr>
		    </thead>
		    <tbody>
		      <tr>
			<th scope="row">Old COLA rate</th>
			<td>{old_cola}</td>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			<th scope="row">New COLA rate</th>
			<td>{new_cola}</td>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			<th scope="row">Effective date</th>
			<td>{date}</td>
		      </tr>
			  <th scope="row">Country name</th>
			<td>{country}</td>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			  <th scope="row">Post name</th>
			<td>{post}</td>
		      </tr>
		    </tbody>
		  </table>
		</div>
	      </p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	  <div class="usa-accordion faq-accordion">
	    <h2 class="usa-accordion__heading">
              <button class="usa-accordion__button faq-accordion-button"
		      aria-expanded="false"
		      aria-controls="a4">
		<span class="font-xl" style="font-weight: lighter">Q.</span>
		Do I have to upload a template?
              </button>
	    </h2>
	    <div id="a4" class="usa-accordion__content usa-prose">
              <p>No, you do not have to upload a template to use this tool. We provide a default template in the template dropdown which users may choose as the preferred template for a subscription.</p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	  <div class="usa-accordion faq-accordion">
	    <h2 class="usa-accordion__heading">
              <button class="usa-accordion__button faq-accordion-button"
		      aria-expanded="false"
		      aria-controls="a5">
		<span class="font-xl" style="font-weight: lighter">Q.</span>
		Can I reuse templates?
              </button>
	    </h2>
	    <div id="a5" class="usa-accordion__content usa-prose">
              <p>Yes! After uploading a template on the <a class="usa-link" href="/subscriptions">subscriptions</a> page (while creating a new subscription), we will save this template for you and you will then be able to select this template when creating or modifying subscriptions.</p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>
      </div> 
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- Modal -->
  <div class="modal fade" id="previewTemplateModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="previewTemplates" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
      <div class="modal-content">
	<div class="modal-header">
          <h2 class="h5 modal-title" id="previewTemplateLabel"></h2>
          <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
            <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
          </button>
	</div>
	<div class="modal-body">
	  <div id="previewCanvasContainer" class="d-flex justify-content-center">
	    <div id="canvasSpinnerContainer">
	    </div>
	    <div class="container">
	      <div class="row justify-content-start justify-content-md-around">
		<canvas id="previewCanvas" class="mb-4"></canvas>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
